          Cloud Power has no capital expenditure implications for the Power Companies and the insurance premium is much lower than the cost of same sized power stations.  
          There is a good scope for governments to subsidise the feed-in tariffs and/or equipment cost, expanding the market exponentially to smaller users.  
          Design smaller and more economical equipment for the smaller customers with special attention to cost effective installation and maintenance.
          The installation cost does not scale well with more clients but this could be reduced by making equipment for self-installation. 
          </p>
        </div>
