          Our servers will continuously update the available capacity per region to the dispatchers, who can then give selective and partial shed commands.  
          The Power Companies pay an insurance premium of less than two percent per year of the cost of a similar sized new generation plant. 
          Initial supply contracts will be for a period of three years to cover the installation and modifications costs. 
          The price for the energy will be comparable to the marginal cost for peaking-Power Stations. 
          The Power Companies recover some of the money by reselling the power to customers after the crisis or peak, at a lower rate. (All envisaged loads are recoverable loads.)  
          Geo-location will be used to quickly alleviate overload conditions in regions of the grid.  
